today i learned about azure storage services

## Objective
Understand different types of Azure storage and their use cases

## Topics Covered
- Blob Storage (object storage for unstructured data)
- Disk Storage (used by virtual machines)
- File Storage (managed file shares using SMB)
- Queue Storage (messaging between application components)
- Table Storage (NoSQL key-value storage)
- Data Lake Storage (optimized for big data analytics)
- Archive Storage (low-cost storage for rarely accessed data)
- Data Box (used for transferring large amounts of data physically)

## Key Differences I Learned

- Blob vs File:
  - Blob = object storage (images, videos)
  - File = shared file system (like network drive)

- Queue vs Table:
  - Queue = messaging system
  - Table = NoSQL structured storage

- Disk vs Blob:
  - Disk = attached to VM
  - Blob = independent storage

## Real-World Use Cases

- Blob → storing app images/videos
- File → shared company folder
- Queue → decoupling services (background jobs) ( application messaging system)
- Table → storing unstructered nosql data
- Archive → backups
- Data Lake → analytics workloads

## Key Takeaways
- Azure storage is not one service → multiple types for different needs
- Choosing wrong storage can impact cost and performance

